title: PML-N’s Sardar Parvez Iqbal wins PP-294 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate, Sardar Parvez Iqbal Gorchani has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-294, Rajanpur-III by securing 43,648 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate, Muhammad Atif Ali Dareshak who bagged 30,528 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 48.71%.
